HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 249
BY REPRESENTATIVE FISHER
A RESOLUTION
To urge and request the State Board of Elementary and Secondary Education to incorporate
artificial intelligence (AI) into content standards.
WHEREAS, AI is transforming every major sector of the economy and shaping the
future of work, civic life, and global competitiveness; preparing students for this new reality
requires that educators have both a foundational understanding of AI and access to
instructional resources that are age- and grade-appropriate and incorporated into academic
instruction in an intentional manner; and
WHEREAS, ensuring that exploration of AI is done in a safe, private, and ethical
way in schools is imperative; and
WHEREAS, the responsible integration of AI into K-12 education is essential to
building a future-ready workforce and ensuring Louisiana remains competitive in science,
technology, engineering, mathematics, and many other fields.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request the State Board of Elementary and
Secondary Education to incorporate artificial intelligence into content standards.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
